HEADWORD: jive
<hw>jive</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>a style of jazz played by big bands
popular in the 1930s; flowing rhythms but less complex than later styles
of jazz.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> swing, swing music.</syn>⟦br⟧
